description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Solent NHS Trust Estates Premises Team in &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Southampton&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;are seeking 2 enthusiastic and customer focussed Reception Supervisors. This role is an exciting opportunity to join a forward-thinking Trust and Premises Team at a time of exciting change within the NHS.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will see the successful candidate based at Western Community Campus &amp; also at Bitterne Health Centre in Southampton but supporting remotely buildings across Hampshire &amp; the Isle of Wight. The successful candidates will be Line Managers for reception teams based on the Western Community Hospital, Adelaide Health Centre &amp; Pickles Coppice in the West of the city &amp;. Bitterne Health Centre &amp; Thornhill Centre for Healthy Living to the East of the city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will be highly motivated individuals, capable of working independently and as part of a wider team. They will be approachable and highly customer focussed and take pride in the attractive appearance and smooth operation of Estates Site Management. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Under the guidance of the Estates Premises Manager they will support the operation of buildings and development of a customer focused highly utilised environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Marie Ames on marie.ames@solent.nhs.uk for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier date. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage.&lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not been selected.&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders.&lt;/p&gt;
